# Personal Project Instructions

## Personal Project Preferences

### Project Management
- No ticket requirement for personal projects
- Flexible commit message format (conventional commits optional but encouraged)
- Experimentation and learning encouraged
- Simpler PR process — description can be brief for solo projects

### Technology Flexibility
- Open to different stacks and tools
- Can use any database technology (PostgreSQL, SQLite, MongoDB, etc.)
- Free to try new frameworks, libraries, and approaches

### Documentation
- README is sufficient for most personal projects
- Detailed docs only when the project grows or is intended for sharing

## Cloud Provider Safety

No personal cloud account is considered safe for auto-execution. Before running any cloud CLI command:

1. **Present the commands** — List exactly what will be run and why
2. **Flag write operations** — If any command modifies infrastructure (create, update, delete, deploy, destroy), explicitly call this out
3. **Wait for confirmation** — Do not execute until the user approves

Read-only commands still require presenting the command and rationale, but should be noted as read-only.
